author: National Geographic
description:
The port city of Hull in Yorkshire, England, has undergone a significant revitalization over the last decade, bringing the city's maritime past to the forefront. The town's cultural and historic highlights are on full display in its Georgian Old Town, Museums Quarter, and celebrated aquarium and marine conservation center.

author: National Geographic
description:
Paid content for @PepsiCo. How can agriculture work together with nature? Join National Geographic photographer Rena Effendi as she travels to Brazil and meets with a local farming family to learn ways they are creating a more sustainable farm. From planting trees along with crops to mimic natural forest systems to improving the biology of the soil for growing corn, they are discovering how plants can work together.

author: National Geographic
description:
The five families of New York City continue to run the American mob with an iron fist, a million scams, and a booming resort town named Atlantic City. The gambling mecca is overseen by the Philadelphia mob, which answers directly to New York. But when an old school Philadelphia don named Angelo Bruno is assassinated in 1980, a bloody new era begins.
